ted the Treaty of Fort Laramie that ended Red Cloud's War. He then served as the last military governor of the Third Military District at Atlanta in 1869, where he was a strong opponent of the Ku Klux Klan."},{"number":5,"category":"family","header":"His line ended at New Haven, no children","body":"He died at New Haven in December 1890 at age 63, having never had children. His siblings included Harriet Wadsworth Terry and Jeremiah Wadsworth Terry, names their father chose for the Wadsworth-Hooker ancestry."}],"former_ids":[],"education":[],"career":[],"is_placeholder":false,"slug":"alfred-terry-1827"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}